<subSubSection id="CE8DB8D8FFFBA13365CFFE2EB96809EF" pageId="2" pageNumber="135" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8628EB53FFFBA13365CFFE2EB96809EF" blockId="2.[151,1436,405,502]" pageId="2" pageNumber="135">
<emphasis id="B4E33741FFFBA13365CFFE2EBD5009CB" bold="true" box="[199,321,441,466]" pageId="2" pageNumber="135">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The male of 
<taxonomicName id="419790D0FFFBA13364DEFE2EBEF309CB" box="[470,738,441,466]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Brachypogon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="freidbergi">
<emphasis id="B4E33741FFFBA13364DEFE2EBEF309CB" box="[470,738,441,466]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="135">Brachypogon freidbergi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinct in having elongate slender apicolateral processes of tergite 
<number id="305FF974FFFBA13365EDFE49BCE409EF" box="[229,245,478,502]" pageId="2" pageNumber="135" value="9.0">9</number>
, and a deeply forked Y-shaped gonostylus that resembles obtuse crayfish claws. Females are unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="D2E8BBDBFFFBA133659FF806BF280FDF" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/227558/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="135" targetBox="[151,1436,554,1915]" targetPageId="2">
